<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0dbb6925-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s2306"><num value="2306">§ 2306.</num><heading> Special rule</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In the case of a local community in which no employees are represented by a labor organization, for purposes of this chapter, the term “representatives of employees” shall be substituted for “labor organization”.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0dbb6926-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/210/s7">Pub. L. 88–210, § 7</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/109/270/s1/b">Pub. L. 109–270, § 1(b)</ref>, <date date="2006-08-12">Aug. 12, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/690">120 Stat. 690</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0dbb6927-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id0dbb6928-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id0dbb6929-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior section 2306, <ref href="/us/pl/88/210/s7">Pub. L. 88–210, § 7</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/105/332/s1/b">Pub. L. 105–332, § 1(b)</ref>, <date date="1998-10-31">Oct. 31, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/3083">112 Stat. 3083</ref>, related to special rule, prior to the general amendment of this chapter by <ref href="/us/pl/109/270">Pub. L. 109–270</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
